<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Exemplar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">how do i get from the city of Halas to the city of Qeynos. i am looking for a safe rout to take to...i am only lvl 2 right now</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alsk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sorry bud but you got no chance....the only way to get through is to go through bb....everything there (except pups) will be tombstone to you...in fact...there are 4 guards outside of bb...so youll probaly never make it inside...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakshot</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Best advice, stay in Halas till 5.  The newbie area in Halas is one of the best, assuming you survive.  The unholy proliferation of those stupid polar bear cubs makes you level, or die.<P>Then, at level 5, print out Muse's map of Everfrost.  It's not as hard as you'd think.  Oh yeah, run like hell.  If you meet one of the Composers or other tormented band members, you're hosed.  The gnolls inside Blackburrow and outside both entrances are gonna want a piece of you, too.  I'd wait for a primetime playing time, say after school gets out, or on a weekend afternoon.  If you can get a SOW from one of your friendly shamans, you'll increase your chances of survival drastically.  Just don't beg them over tells, there's nothing more annoying in the game.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alsk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oakshot is much wiser ( and more considerate) than me =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Malisenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Don't fret about hanging around Everfrost for a few more levels... seriously, it's an awesome place to lvl easily from 1-5 in particular. It only took me 2-3 hours to do so with my Shaman and that includes some time spent exploring Halas itself. I suggest paying attention to the polar bear cubs and spiderlings, they're good xp. And take all white bear pelts you loot to Cindl in the kilt shop for even more xp, pieces of armor, and money. <P>Although Qeynos is worth going to, right now you'll earn a lot in Everfrost for now.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Telen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loved Halas in that mola and xp was great and it was such an easy run back to my corpse. I also recommneding that you group with others. <BR>This is a great spot with great hunting. I also dont think you would make it through BB.<P>Telen<BR>Shaman 15th Winter(Though it seems always to be winter)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
